<DocLayout title="Introduction">
  <h1>Kayoko</h1>
  <p class="lead text-xl text-slate-400">
    Kayoko is a POSIX-compliant, fast, secure, and highly portable Unix-like system.
  </p>

  <h2>Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>RBAC</strong> (via KAT - Kernel Access Table)</li>
    <li><strong>SMAT</strong> (System Manager for Administrative Tools)</li>
    <li>NetBSD-based foundations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Getting Started</h2>
  <p>To learn how to compile and test the system, please view the <a href="/docs/build">Building Documentation</a>.</p>

